\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Calibration of Cox-Ingersoll-Ross Process 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
hyperlink{Calibration-Strategy}{
\backslash
beamergotobutton{Back}}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "appendix: CIR"

\end_inset

We fit the following process:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\textrm{d}z_{t}=-\theta_{z,s}\left(z_{t}-\underset{=1}{\underbrace{z^{d}}}\right)\textrm{d}t+\sigma_{z,s}\sqrt{z_{t}}\textrm{d}W_{t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 1: use Computstat Data (1950-2019) and build 
\begin_inset Formula $K_{ist}$
\end_inset

 using perpetual inventory method with linear interpolation of investment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 2: estimate TFP as residual from the following regression:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\log\left(\text{sales}_{ist}\right)=\gamma_{i}+f_{st}+\alpha_{s}\log\left(\text{emp}_{ist}\right)+\beta_{s}\log\left(K_{is,t-1}\right)+\varepsilon_{ist}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 3: fit a firm specific Linear Trend on the estimated series to focus
 on idiosyncratic component of TFP
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 4: estimate parameters of CIR process by Maximum Likelihood, using
 a procedure adapted from Wei et alii (2016)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Multi-Sector Equilibrium: Limit Case 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
hyperlink{Calibration-Strategy}{
\backslash
beamergotobutton{Back}}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame

\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "appendix: psi"

\end_inset

Most (if not all) firms today are 
\emph on
not 
\emph default
fully automated.
 Model is analytically tractable if 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{s}\left(\check{z}_{s}\right)\approx0$
\end_inset

.
\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Can show almost all firms 
\emph on
within each sector
\emph default
 choose the same sector-specific stock:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
R\approx R_{\max,s}^{\star}=\frac{1}{\psi_{R}\delta}\left[\frac{\Omega_{s}}{\rho+\delta}-p_{R}\right]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proposition*
Consider the general equilibrium model with 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{s}\left(\check{z}_{s}\right)\rightarrow0$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $θ_{s}=θ$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $s$
\end_inset

, and elasticity of substitution across industries 
\begin_inset Formula $σ=1$
\end_inset

.
 In the neighborhood of an equilibrium supported by prices 
\begin_inset Formula $(w,\mathbf{p})$
\end_inset

, aggregate equilibrium labor is increasing in 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{R}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{R}$
\end_inset

, and aggregate robot penetration is decreasing in 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{R}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{R}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Calibration of 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{R}/w$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
hyperlink{Calibration-Strategy}{
\backslash
beamergotobutton{Back}}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
We show that in the limit case discussed above,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\tilde{\Gamma_{s}}\left(\frac{\psi_{R}}{w}\right)=\left[1+\frac{m}{w}+\left(\rho+\delta\right)\left(\delta\frac{\psi_{R}}{w}\left(\frac{R}{L}\right)_{s,2014}\xi_{s}+\left(\frac{p_{R}}{w}\right)_{2014}\right)\right]^{-1}
\]

\end_inset

So, assuming at the true 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}$
\end_inset

 the equilibrium is such that the limit case is approximately verified,
 then:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 1: Guess initial value for 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{\psi_{R}}{w}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 2: Find equilibrium prices and wage in 2010 and 2014 setting 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}=\tilde{\Gamma}_{s}$
\end_inset

 and fixing the relative robot prices at their respective levels
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 3: Compute aggregate robot penetration in 2010 and 2014 and the deviation
 from the percentage change in the data
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 4: Update guess and go back to Step 2 until convergence
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Calibration of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
hyperlink{Calibration-Strategy}{
\backslash
beamergotobutton{Back}}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "appendix: gamma"

\end_inset

The calibration of the sector-specific 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}$
\end_inset

 follows that of 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{R}/w$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 1: Guess initial value of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}$
\end_inset

 using 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{\Gamma}_{s}$
\end_inset

 evaluated at the calibrated 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi_{R}/w$
\end_inset

 as starting point
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 2: Find equilibrium prices and wage that clear the markets in 
\begin_inset Formula $2014$
\end_inset

 given 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}$
\end_inset

 and the relative robot price 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{R}/w$
\end_inset

 in 2014.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 3: Compute deviation of sector specific 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(R/L\right)_{s}$
\end_inset

 from their targets 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Step 4: Update guesses 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{s}$
\end_inset

 and go back to Step 2 until convergence
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
